ed if some of the field sources\nwere generated in situ. We show that isolated accreting very massive black\nholes are unlikely to be observable with current X-ray instrumentation and that\nthese sources hence do not contaminate the LMXB population. We discuss the\npossibility that several equatorial point sources may indicate the presence of\na disk wind responsible for the low radiative efficiency observed in the\nnucleus of this source. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Oct 2002 10:26:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Dec 2002 13:47:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
