{"id":"nlin/0210007","submitter":"Joseph A. Biello","authors":"Peter R. Kramer, Joseph A. BIello and Yury Lvov","title":"Application of Weak Turbulence Theory to FPU Model","comments":"10 pages, to appear \"Proceedings of the Fourth International\n  Converence on Dynamical Systems and Differential Equations\"","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.CD","license":null,"abstract":"  The foundations of weak turbulence theory is explored through its application\nto the (alpha) Fermi-Pasta-Ulam (FPU) model, a simple weakly nonlinear\ndispersive system. A direct application of the standard kinetic equations would\nmiss interesting dynamics of the energy transfer process starting from a\nlarge-scale excitation. This failure is traced to an enforcement of the exact\nresonance condition, whereas mathematically the resonance should be broadened\ndue to the energy transfer happening on large but finite time scales. By\nallowing for the broadened resonance, a modified three-wave kinetic equation is\nderived for the FPU model. This kinetic equation produces some correct scaling\npredictions about the statistical dynamics of the FPU model, but does not model\naccurately the detailed evolution of the energy spectrum. The reason for the\nfailure seems not to be one of the previously clarified reasons for breakdown\nin the weak turbulence theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Oct 2002 14:42:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
